  <h1>Monocrystalline Silicon Boules</h1>
  <h3>Source</h3>
  <text>
    <style color="0xaaaaaa" italic="true">Note: this page is ported from MCMOD's GTCEu wiki.<br></br>Author: <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://center.mcmod.cn/179043/">花海</style>, <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://center.mcmod.cn/508290/">morningglory</style>, <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://github.com/Yefancy">KilaBash</style><br></br>, <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://github.com/blackdragon2447">BlackDragon2447</style><br></br></style>
  </text>
  <h2>Crafting and Usage</h2>
  <text>A Monocrystalline silicon boule is made by smelting 32 <style color="0xbbffaa">silicon dusts</style> in an <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:multiblock/electric_blast_furnace" underlined="true">Electric Blast Furnace</style> with a small pile of <style color="0xbbffaa">gallium arsenide dusts</style>, requires a minimum coil temperature of <style color="0xff5555">1,784 K</style> to perform the process and can be smelted using the Cupronickel Coil.</text>
  <recipe id="gtceu:electric_blast_furnace/silicon_boule"></recipe>
  <br></br>
  <text>One monocrystalline silicon boule can be cut into 16 <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:circuits/wafers" underlined="true">silicon wafers</style> in a <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/cutter" underlined="true">cutter</style>, which also requires a minimum MV voltage to process.</text>
  <recipe id="gtceu:cutter/cut_silicon_boule_water"></recipe>
  <br></br>
  <h2>Boule Doping</h2>
  <text>Boules can be doped with various materials, their <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:circuits/wafers" underlined="true">wafers</style> are required for higher tier circuits. These boules require a <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:multiblock/cleanroom" underlined="true">Cleanroom</style> to be cut into wafers. The materials used for doping of boules are, in tiered order:</text>
  <br></br>
  <h3>Phosphorus</h3>
  <text>These boules can be produced, cut and engraved at HV and require nitrogen as an inert gas in the <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:multiblock/electric_blast_furnace" underlined="true">EBF</style>.</text>
  <recipe id="gtceu:electric_blast_furnace/phosphorus_boule"></recipe>
  <recipe id="gtceu:cutter/cut_phosphorus_boule_water"></recipe>
  <h3>Naquadah</h3>
  <text>These boules can be produced, cut and engraved at EV and require argon as an inert gas in the <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:multiblock/electric_blast_furnace" underlined="true">EBF</style>.</text>
  <recipe id="gtceu:electric_blast_furnace/naquadah_boule"></recipe>
  <recipe id="gtceu:cutter/cut_naquadah_boule_water"></recipe>
  <h3>Neutronium</h3>
  <text>These boules can be produced, cut and engraved at IV and require xenon as an inert gas in the <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:multiblock/electric_blast_furnace" underlined="true">EBF</style>.</text>
  <recipe id="gtceu:electric_blast_furnace/neutronium_boule"></recipe>
  <recipe id="gtceu:cutter/cut_neutronium_boule_water"></recipe>
</page>
